-------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Oh no you didn't!"
ERROR :: rungms.gms file not found. Please make one.
=========================================================================

Create a new txt file called rungms.gms in this directory.
This file will contain information about your GAMESS setup.

The format of this file is:
VARIABLE=VALUE

The file must contain:
GAMESSDIR=C:\Path\to\this\directory
AUXDATADIR=C:\Path\to\your\local\auxdata\directory
RESTARTDIR=C:\Path\to\your\local\restart\directory
SCRATCHDIR=C:\Path\to\your\local\scratch\directory

GAMESSDIR is the path to the GAMESS directory.  You should know it
since you just executed the 'rungms.bat' file that is contained in
this directory.

RESTARTDIR is the path to the directory where you wish to save
the GAMESS restart files (.dat, .rst, .trj, .efp, .gamma, .ldos)

SCRATCHDIR is the path to the directory GAMESS will use
to store scratch files (which gets deleted at the end of a run).

Additional parameters:
        DEBUG=[TRUE,FALSE] Option for extra printing from this script.
       HEADER=[TRUE,FALSE] Option to 'show'/'not show' the GAMESS banner.
      SUPRESS=[TRUE,FALSE] Option to 'not show'/'show' the job's
                           environmental variable list.
ERASEOLDFILES=[TRUE,FALSE] Option to allow the script to remove old restart
                           files if they are found.
CLEANALLLOCAL=[TRUE,FALSE] Option to remove the job's environmental variable
                           and MPI config file.
=========================================================================

Now exiting.
